<br>
I read under the quest section here that while waiting for Hasten to appear, the alternate spawns (Place Holders) are<br>
<br>
-A Drake (common)<br>
-Named unkempt Druid (second most common)<br>
-Hasten (3rd)<br>
-Brother Zephyl (rare)<br>
<br>
It took me around 9 hours over three days to finally see Hasten (and get my boots - Yay <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ).  During that time, I was PK'd twice - ouch 750pp gone (I play on Tallon Zek)  and went LD 3 times (off to get a new rapier..grrr).<br>
<br>
I have to disagree with the spawn times posted in the quest info.  The Drake is correct - spawned heaps of times.  I only saw the Unkempt Druid (can't remember his name) once.  Brother Zephyl spawned 4 times (long wait for him to go away), and of course Hasten spawned once.  Admittedly I was not on 24 hours and may have just been unlucky (certainly was with getting PK'd), but after spending such a long time there, maybe the spawn rates have changed recently.  <br>
<br>
Not sure, but I thought I would share my experience for anyone about to go and hand in their stuff for the ring.  Hope it is not as long and frustrating a wait as I had.<br>
<br>
